Major Contributors
------------------
We like to thank the following people especially, since they made
significant contributions to the ATK project.

Stefan Niederhauser <sn@atelier-w.ch>

  Stefan came up with the idea of the 'node' concept, which later
  became the basis of the ATK backend.

William Rhee <willrhee@umich.edu>

  William, of the University of Michigan, added Oracle 8i Support
  to Achievo.

Ber Dohmen <info@ibuildings.nl>

  Ber developed the DHTML menu, and created a menu abstraction layer,
  during an internship at ibuildings.nl.

Mark Baaijens <mark@ibuildings.nl>

  Mark added the atkSecureRelation (Privacy Enhancing Technology)
  and the atk/security/encryption tools.

Yury Golovnya <YGolovnya@kyiv.utel.com.ua>

  Yury contributed a large number of patches for numerous errors and features.

Guido van Biemen <guido@ibuildings.nl>

  Guido, among other things, integrated the TinyButStrong Open Office
  template engine in ATK, made ATK largely notice free and fixed a significant
  amount of bugs.


